$ desktop.ini

The `desktop.ini` file can be used to customize some aspects of a *folder*, for example its icon.

In order for the `desktop.ini` file to have any effect, it needs the *system* attribute set. This attribut can be set with the
→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/attrib_exe[`attrib.exe +s desktop.ini`]


code {
[.ShellClassInfo]
IconResource=…
code }
